cs.CR, cs.GT, cs.IT, cs.DC, cs.AI

Reasoning: 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on privacy-preserving techniques for spectrum auctions.
- cs.GT (Game Theory and Economics) is also likely as the paper discusses the socially efficient double spectrum auction design.
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is relevant as the paper uses homomorphic encryption and secret sharing techniques.
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) may be relevant as the paper discusses a two-party protocol for computing the auction.
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) may be relevant as the paper discusses the use of garbled circuits in the auction design.
